2. cs.CE (Circuit Design, Simulation, and Performance): The paper discusses the design and control of RLC and s-RLC circuits, which is related to circuit design and performance. 
3. cs.ET (Electronics and Electrical Engineering): The paper deals with the control of electrical circuits, which falls under the category of electronics and electrical engineering. 
4. cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): Although the paper is focused on electrical circuits, the proposed control methodologies can also be applied to mechanical systems, which falls under the category of mechanical engineering. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): This category is less likely, but the paper does mention the design of voltage controllers for DC networks, which could be related to distributed computing.
